communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The key statement in the above media report is "Bacterial/fungal infections or other diseases found in the dead ducks could be secondary infections caused as a result of a primary virus infection". We hope the current tests in India's NIHSAD (Bhopal) laboratories will discover the virus behind the undiagnosed deaths of ducks, described above. One of the main candidate suspects is HPAI H5N8, spreading into multiple Eurasian countries during the seasonal migration of wild birds. In case confirmed, the apparent absence of disease in other poultry species will have to be clarified. - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Kerala State, India: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8059148,308.]
